message:
I'm a bit uncertain to why Task.Run is used, since this uses a new thread. Wouldn't the "right" async-await pattern try to avoid that?

There probably is a very good reason which I would like to know as to why the following constructor isn't there:  
/// <summary>  
/// Initializes a new instance of the <see cref="AsyncLazy&lt;T&gt;"/> class.  
/// </summary>  
/// <param name="factory">The asynchronous delegate that is invoked to produce the value when it is needed.</param>  
public AsyncLazy(Func<task<t>> factory)  
{  
instance = new Lazy<task<t>>(factory);  
}
